cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "Sillok: A Productized LLM Wiki Pattern with Two-Stage Routing and Proposal-Only Governance"
message: "If you use Sillok in research, please cite it using the metadata below."
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Kim
    given-names: Peter
    email: tykim21@gmail.com
abstract: >-
  Sillok is a productized implementation of Andrej Karpathy's LLM Wiki
  three-layer pattern, extended with a typed pack registry, two-stage
  routing, proposal-only four-gate governance, multi-tenant overlays,
  and a multi-format auto-ingest pipeline (md / pdf / docx / xlsx /
  pptx / txt / hwpx). Its naming evokes a UNESCO Memory of the World
  Triple Anchor (Sillok 1997, Jikji 2001, Janggyeong 2007) for a
  cultural identity rooted in immutable, audit-friendly knowledge
  governance.
keywords:
  - large-language-models
